tinib should be reduced by 50% when used concomitantly with one or more medications that may result in both moderate inhibition of CYP450 3A4 and potent inhibition of CYP450 2C19.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/105761/', '', 'Tinidazole, Pantoprazole, Levofloxacin, Dexlansoprazole, Rabeprazole, Sucralfate, Tetracycline, Misoprostol, Bismuth subcitrate potassium, Metronidazole, Famotidine, More', 'Golimumab, Ustekinumab, Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Canakinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Abatacept, Upadacitinib, Siponimod, More', 1767369485);
